  <title>ideal gas</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Gas which obeys the equation of state pV = nRT (the ideal gas law; p is the pressure, V the volume, n the amount of molecules, R the gas constant and T the thermodynamic temperature). For an ideal gas the fugacity, f, of each constituentB is equal to its partial pressure, pB,fB = pB = xB.p, where xB is the amount fraction of B.</text>
